<sect1 xml:id="MigratingTo3" version='5.0' xmlns='http://docbook.org/ns/docbook'
       xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
       xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
       xsi:schemaLocation="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook http://www.docbook.org/xml/5.0/xsd/docbook.xsd
      http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink.xsd">
    <title>Migrating to Hazelcast 3.0</title>
    <para>
        In this section, we list the changes what users should take into account before upgrading to Hazelcast 3.0 from
        earlier versions of Hazelcast.
    </para>
    <para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <emphasis role="bold">Removal of deprecated static methods:</emphasis>
                <para>
                    The static methods of Hazelcast class reaching hazelcast data components have been removed.
                    Removed methods:
                    <itemizedlist>
                        <listitem>
                            Hazelcast.init(Config config);
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            Hazelcast.getDefaultInstance();
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            Hazelcast.getQueue(String name);
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            Hazelcast.getTopic(String name);
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            Hazelcast.getSet(String name);
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            Hazelcast.getList(String name);
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            Hazelcast.getMap(String name);
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            Hazelcast.getMultiMap(String name);
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            Hazelcast.getLock(String name);
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            Hazelcast.getMap(String name);
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            Hazelcast.getMap(String name);
                        </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
                </para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
    </para>
</sect1>
